        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasco_County%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The county takes its name from Senator Samuel Pasco, elected to the Senate in 1887, though he never visited.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pasco_County%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "When Pasco County was created, Dade City served as its temporary county seat before the capital moved.",
